<h2>The Angry Hive</h2>

<p>Unfortunately this is inevitable. You will have a hive that is angry. You can't get near the hive. There are many reasons why this can happen in a colony.</p>

<ul>
 <li><h3>Congestion:</h3> <p>When a hive gets crowded the girls will be    aggressive.     Especially if flow has suddenly stopped.</p>
 <p>What to do.</p>
    <ul>
	<li>Reduce the size by splitting. You can take off some brood and it will give you brood boost a hive if needed.</li>
	<li>Give them more space. If there are lots of bees just the addition of a box can help.</li><a href="https://beemaster.ca/cgi-bin/index.cgi?site=BMaster&page=SpringSlits" target="_Blank">spliting hives</a></li>
</ul>
